        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 19, 2026</p>

        <p>Quoryx Services ("we," "our," or "us") operates quoryx.net. This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our website and the choices you have associated with that data.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Email addresses:</strong> When you join our waitlist, we collect your email address to contact you about our product launch and updates.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> We may collect information about how you access and use our website, including your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time spent on pages.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected data for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To communicate with you about Quoryx product development and launch</li>
            <li>To provide customer support and respond to your inquiries</li>
            <li>To improve our website and services</li>
            <li>To monitor and analyze usage patterns</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>Your data is stored securely and we implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information. We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.</p>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We do not currently share your data with third-party services. When our product launches and integrates with accounting platforms (Xero, QuickBooks), we will update this policy accordingly and notify all users.</p>

        <h2>5. GDPR Compliance (EU Users)</h2>
        <p>If you are located in the European Union, you have the following rights:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to access your personal data</li>
            <li>Right to rectification of inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
            <li>Right to data portability</li>
            <li>Right to object to processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:tech@quoryx.net">tech@quoryx.net</a>.</p>

        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your email address until you request deletion or unsubscribe from our communications. You may request deletion of your data at any time by contacting us.</p>

        <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
        <p>Our website does not currently use cookies. If this changes, we will update this policy and provide notice.</p>

        <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our service is not directed to individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

        <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.</p>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:tech@quoryx.net">tech@quoryx.net</a><br>
